Hell.. it should look like me... it's my Mom!! So watch it!<br>
Haven't picked up on the transmission... my electronic iron don't do me right!  Meant to back mail Cookie a letter bomb.. can't figure out how to do it!  Besides, Turkeys are not in season.<br><br>
Thank you Paul.. just the kind of stuff we needed.  Great post!<br><br>
I feel that I attained a level of greatness.. impossible to achieve without the challenge placed before me by warfare.  Also, I feel that I have journeyed to the lowest level of human frailty because of the things I did and failed to do in Vietnam.  One can read about war.. hear words such as courage.. sacrifice.. fear.. shame.. anger, but only until one lives the horror can they truly understand and receive the full impact.  I, too, am a good father.. as I suspect Cookie, John and the others to be.  That is the most important lesson for me.  In protecting freedom, in general, with its vague and sometimes poor strategies.. I have learned some hard lessons.  In protecting those things closest to my heart I have found the need for a clear set of rules.. seek the truth and try to live by the blueprints, formulas, and receipes that truth presents.  Denial and that confusion that comes from emotional upheaval has caused me to loose sight of the truth on occassions.<br>
The losses I suffered in Vietnam help me to appreciate what I have today (count your blessings type stuff!)  Above all, that trip across the pond to SEA taught me what others have done for me in that war and previous wars.<br>
Above all, I have learned to love my brothers with a sense of unconditional positive regard that comes close to that of my God, but far short of his true glory... because I cannot yet love everyone.<br><br>
Thanks, PP (or is it Pee Pee? ...Good grief, you guys have the weirdest names...)<br><br>
